				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">doynax wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Neighter of these seems to be used in Megaman (well.. the early games had split screen). Yet Capcom chose to use horizontal mirroring, why?</div>
<br />
<br />The only Megaman with hardwired mirroring is the original (which uses an UNROM board) and it uses vertical mirroring.  The other games in the series all have mapper-controlled mirroring.   I haven't checked but I suspect they use vertical mirroring everywhere, except perhaps in some boss battles.  Remember that none of the NES Megaman games has any smooth vertical scrolling sequences--vertical scrolling is always in screen-sized chunks.
<br />
<br />Also, the only Megaman game with a split screen is Megaman 3.  The first two games draw the weapon-select window right on top of the BG (like the subscreen in Zelda 2) and the last three switch to a completely separate screen.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

