					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Wait, I spoke too soon.  The later Megaman games must use <em>horizontal</em> mirroring in regular gameplay--because of the subscreen in MM3, and in the later games for split screen gimmicks (e.g. the "crushing ceiling" sequence which SMB3 popularized)
<br />
<br />The MM games from MM3 onward all clip the leftmost 8-pixel column via bits 2 and 1 of $2001, and have tile and palette artifacts at the rightmost edge of the screen--the two unmistakable signs that a game is doing horizontal scrolling with horizontal mirroring.</div>

